Ok take it easy on me. And, I’m leaving a lot open so that those with DPS/DPM information can make changes.<br>
<br>
All pets post -50 should fight as if they were a Mob of equal level. A 51st level Summon Earth Elemental <br>
spell  should summon a 51st level Elemental.  Damage and hit points can stay the same if they like or bump <br>
them up if they like. But the attack level, needs to be addressed. This way our pets can hit with near full <br>
effect on Mobs  Again, I’m only talking about the pets level for attack not in totality of hit points or damage.  This will help the Fire Elemental to stick it’s spells and not be useless due to it being a 41st to 45th level Mob. Trying to effect Mobs of a much higher level.<br>
<br>
A line of spells that mirror the Summon spells after 50th.  These spells will let us summon the sprite of a elemental to ourselves.  This will let us for 400 mana be able to have the spell Attack of that Elemental while it is bound to our body. No graphics needed as there is no elemental persent. Just the one inside of us.<br>
 We couldn’t summon a pet while this spell is in effect. Here is a example:<br>
<br>
51st level. Quilin cast, Quilin’s Earth Elemental Binding. (Cast Time=X, Recast Time=Y, Mana=400(equal to summoning a pet). Quilin’s eyes glow with elemental fury, rage,  blah, blah. From this point each time I cast this spell again for say 250 mana (?) I can do a Earth Elemental Attack: Range 200 Damage 800(?) with a 3-6second Root (?) Attack type Magic (?)<br>
 <br>
52nd level. Quilin cast, Quilin’s Fire Elemental Binding. (Cast Time=X, Recast Time=Y, Mana=400(equal to summoning a pet). Quilin’s eyes glow with elemental fury, rage,  blah, blah. From this point each time I cast this spell again for say 250 mana (?) I can do a Fire Elemental Attack: Range 200 Damage 1100(?) Attack type Fire (?)<br>
<br>
53rd level. Quilin cast, Quilin’s Air Elemental Binding. (Cast Time=X, Recast Time=Y, Mana=400(equal to summoning a pet). Quilin’s eyes glow with elemental fury, rage,  blah, blah. From this point each time I cast this spell again for say 250 (?) mana I can do a Air Elemental Attack: Range 200 Damage 900 (?) with a 3-6 second Stun (?) Attack type Magic (?)   <br>
<br>
54th level. Quilin cast, Quilin’s Water Elemental Binding. (Cast Time=X, Recast Time=Y, Mana=400 (equal to summoning a pet). Quilin’s eyes glow with elemental fury, rage,  blah, blah. From this point each time I cast this spell again for say 250 mana (?) I can do a Water Elemental Attack: Range 200 Damage 1000 (?) Attack type Cold (?)<br>
<br>
Now please play with the numbers all you want. But this solves the problem of raids. It increases our combat abilities and doesn’t over power us. If you can’t summon a pet with this spell is in effect. It doesn’t change us as a whole  or steps on a Wizard’s ablilities. <br>
<br>
The Epic take it a way as a spell. This is the area that Verant believes makes it so powerful. You can add in a Quilin’s Master Elemental Binding at level Z.<br>
<br>
These are just MY simple ideas.  Thank’s for your time. And Verant can feel free to change any point in these spells. Just not the name…LOL<br>
Quilin 53rd Mage<br>
